  "prompt": "Does masturbation cause loss of memory?",
  "response": "There is no scientific evidence to suggest that masturbation causes loss of memory. Masturbation is a normal and common behavior that many people engage in, and it is generally considered a normal part of human sexuality. While excessive involvement in any activity can potentially lead to negative consequences, such as distractions from responsibilities or studies, there is no direct link between masturbation and memory loss.\n\nIt\u2019s important to differentiate between myths and scientific facts. If you have concerns about memory or cognitive function, it might be helpful to look into other factors such as sleep, stress, nutrition, and overall mental health. If memory issues persist, consulting with a healthcare professional is advisable.",
